{
  "stem": "3848.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But in order for it to be dry-- I have to tell you that the documents were pushed into condoms and tied up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then the document was pushed into the toothpaste from the back, folded it up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in case the Polish government finds us and they arrest us, they wouldn't know that the real-- the other documents that we had to show on the Czechoslovakian side were in the toothpaste.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you squeeze the toothpaste, only toothpaste would come out, and you wouldn't know there was a document.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was one of the tricks that the Bricha had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we came over the border, we landed in a special house in [INAUDIBLE] in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a house already prepared for all of the group.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got washed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We came in in the middle of the night, about 200 people crossing the border.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the morning, the older people and the children were put on trucks, flat beds, covered with canvas over the top.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were lying on the trucks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this way they traveled from [INAUDIBLE] all the way to Bratislava where there was a hotel and specially prepared a place for them to be accepted.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The young people had to go by train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And being that [INAUDIBLE] was a tiny little town with not too many people on the train, they decided to let us out two-by-two-- a boy and a girl.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, young.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were-- as I say, we were young.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we slowly walked towards the station, and we knew when there was going to be a train traveling to Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We showed up on the train two-by-two.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Nobody saw us on the street, but when we got to the station, all of a sudden there was about 100 people.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
